From 52f6de5421f12b70cd54c288796658dc6737e23e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Valerio Setti <vsetti@baylibre.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Apr 2026 23:53:41 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 17/17] include tf_psa_crypto_platform_requirements.h in
 tf_psa_crypto_config.c

This is required because if the user defined configuration file (not the
default one provided by tf-psa-crypto) includes files from the standard
C library then __STDC_WANT_LIB_EXT1__ won't be defined there which
cause weird build failures.

Signed-off-by: Valerio Setti <vsetti@baylibre.com>
---
 core/tf_psa_crypto_config.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/core/tf_psa_crypto_config.c b/core/tf_psa_crypto_config.c
index 95c8ae6a6..be77d72b0 100644
--- a/core/tf_psa_crypto_config.c
+++ b/core/tf_psa_crypto_config.c
@@ -6,6 +6,8 @@
  *  SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 OR GPL-2.0-or-later
  */
 
+#include "tf_psa_crypto_platform_requirements.h"
+
 /* Detect whether this is a normal build of the library, or a build of
  * libtestdriver1, where all identifiers starting with normal prefixes
  * have LIBTESTDRIVER1_ prepended. Do this without relying on
-- 
